@@TJvPreviewControl
<TITLEIMG TJvPreviewControl>
JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.Miscel
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Control that can display a print preview.
Description
  TJvPreviewControl is derived from TJvCustomPreviewControl and publishes most of its properties but
  does not add any new functionality.

  To use a print preview on a form, you must:

    * Drop a TJvPreviewControl on the form
    * Drop one or more renderers derived from TJvCustomPreviewRenderer
    * Connect the <LINK TJvCustomPreviewRenderer.PrintPreview, PrintPreview> with the
      TJvPreviewControl
    * Set the properties of the preview control to your liking
    * At runtime, call <LINK TJvCustomPreviewRenderer.CreatePreview, CreatePreview> to display the
      preview in the TJvPreviewControl.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPageOptions
Summary
  Represents the available options for the pages in the preview control.
Description
  A page in the preview is a visual object that simulates a physical paper page as it would look if
  printed on a printer. The properties of TJvPreviewPageOptions controls the appearance of these
  pages as well as properties pertaining to the relationship between pages in a preview.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPageOptions.Color
Summary
  Specifies the color of the preview pages.
Description
  Use Color to specify the background color for the preview pages.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPageOptions.Cols
Summary
  Indicates the number of pages to display vertically in the visible part of the control.
Description
  Use Cols to specify how many columns of pages should be displayed in the visible part of the
  preview control (without scrolling). Setting Cols may have no effect, either because ScaleMode
  prohibits it or because the number of Rows and Cols requested exceeds the available page count.
See Also
  TJvPreviewPageOptions.Rows, TJvPreviewPageOptions.Scale, TJvPreviewPageOptions.ScaleMode

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPageOptions.DrawMargins
Summary
  Indicates whether print margins are drawn in the preview.
Description
  Use DrawMargins to specify if the preview displays the print margins in the preview. If DrawMargins
  is true, a dotted line is drawn on the preview pages to indicate the printable area.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPageOptions.HorzSpacing
Summary
  Specifies the horizontal distance between pages in the preview.
Description
  Use HorzSpacing to specify the number of pixels between the pages in a preview when the preview is
  displaying more than one page. HorzSpacing is in pixels.
See Also
  TJvPreviewPageOptions.VertSpacing

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPageOptions.OnChange
Summary
  Occurs when any property value is changed.
Description
  Don't write a handler for this event. A handler is assigned internally by the control that created
  the instance.
See Also
  TJvPreviewPageOptions.OnScaleModeChange

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPageOptions.OnScaleModeChange
Summary
  Occurs when the ScaleMode property changes
Description
  Don't write a handler for this event. A handler is assigned internally by the control that created
  the instance.
See Also
  TJvPreviewPageOptions.OnChange

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPageOptions.Rows
Summary
  Indicates the number of pages to display horizontally in the visible part of the control.
Description
  Use Rows to specify how many rows of pages should be displayed in the visible part of the preview
  control (without scrolling). Setting Rows may have no effect, either because ScaleMode prohibits it
  or because the number of Rows and Cols requested exceeds the available page count.
See Also
  TJvPreviewPageOptions.Cols, TJvPreviewPageOptions.Scale, TJvPreviewPageOptions.ScaleMode

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPageOptions.Scale
Summary
  Indicates the scaling of the pages in the preview.
Description
  \Read Scale to determine the current scaling of the pages. Set the value of Scale to change the
  scaling.
  Scale is expressed in percentage.
See Also
  TJvPreviewPageOptions.Cols, TJvPreviewPageOptions.Rows, TJvPreviewPageOptions.ScaleMode

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPageOptions.ScaleMode
Summary
  Indicates the scale mode to use.
Description
  Use ScaleMode to specify how scaling is performed in the preview control. The setting of ScaleMode
  affects how the preview uses the Cols, Rows and Scale properties.
See Also
  TJvPreviewPageOptions.Cols, TJvPreviewPageOptions.Rows, TJvPreviewPageOptions.Scale

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPageOptions.Shadow
Summary
  Reference to settings affecting the page shadow.
Description
  Use Shadow to access the properties that controls the shadow displayed beneath each page.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewPageOptions.VertSpacing
Summary
  Specifies the vertical distance between pages in the preview.
Description
  Use VertSpacing to specify the number of pixels between the pages in a preview when the preview is
  displaying more than one page. VertSpacing is in pixels.
See Also
  TJvPreviewPageOptions.HorzSpacing

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewScaleMode
<TITLE TJvPreviewScaleMode type>
Summary
  The type used for the <LINK TJvPreviewPageOptions.ScaleMode, ScaleMode>
  property in TJvPreviewPageOptions.
Description
  TJvPreviewScaleMode describes the available scale modes for a preview control.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewScaleMode.smFullPage
Display a single page. The page is scaled to fit inside the client area of the control.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewScaleMode.smPageWidth
Display a page so that its width fills the entire client width of the control.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewScaleMode.smScale
Use the <LINK TJvPreviewPageOptions.Scale, Scale> property to determine the size of the page(s) but also use <LINK TJvPreviewPageOptions.Cols, Cols> and <LINK TJvPreviewPageOptions.Rows, Rows>.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewScaleMode.smAutoScale
Use the <LINK TJvPreviewPageOptions.Scale, Scale> property to determine the size of the page(s) and change <LINK TJvPreviewPageOptions.Cols, Cols> and <LINK TJvPreviewPageOptions.Rows, Rows> if necessary.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPreviewScaleMode.smColsRows
Display as many pages as specified by <LINK TJvPreviewPageOptions.Cols, Cols> and <LINK TJvPreviewPageOptions.Rows, Rows> and change <LINK TJvPreviewPageOptions.Scale, Scale> as necessary.

